cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use MABE in your research, please cite it as below."
authors:
  - name: "Luca Popescu"
title: "MABE: Malicious Agent Behavior Emulator"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: 2026
url: "https://github.com/lucapopescu/mabe"
abstract: >
  MABE is a parameterizable synthetic dataset generator for AI-driven
  cyberattacks. It produces labeled event logs emulating the behavioral
  signatures of an AI agent conducting internal network enumeration from
  an assumed breach entry point, contrasted against realistic background
  benign user activity. Empirical parameters are grounded in published
  sources including Anthropic GTG-1002 (November 2025), SANS/Lee
  (December 2025), Dragos (May 2026), and academic research on
  LLM-driven autonomous penetration testing.
keywords:
  - cybersecurity
  - synthetic dataset
  - AI-driven attacks
  - lateral movement
  - behavioral detection
  - SIEM
  - SIFT forensics
license: MIT
